org.jnativehook.keyboard
Class NativeKeyEvent

java.lang.Object
  java.util.EventObject
      org.jnativehook.NativeInputEvent
          org.jnativehook.keyboard.NativeKeyEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class NativeKeyEvent
extends NativeInputEvent

An event which indicates that a keystroke occurred on the system.

This low-level event is generated by the system when a key is pressed or released. The event is passed to every NativeKeyListener object which has been registered to receive such events using the GlobalScreen.addNativeKeyListener(NativeKeyListener) method. Each such listener object gets this NativeKeyEvent when the event occurs.

Since:
1.0
Version:
1.0
Author:
Alexander Barker (alex@1stleg.com)
See Also:
GlobalScreen, NativeKeyListener, Serialized Form

Constructor Detail

NativeKeyEvent

public NativeKeyEvent(int id,
                      long when,
                      int modifiers,
                      int rawCode,
                      int keyCode)
Instantiates a new native key event.

Note that passing in an invalid ID results in unspecified behavior.

Parameters:
id - The type of event.
when - The timestamp for the event.
modifiers - the modifier keys down during event. NativeInputEvent _MASK modifiers should be used as they are not compatible with the extended _DOWN_MASK or the old _MASK InputEvent modifiers.
rawCode - The hardware code associated with the native key in this event.
keyCode - The virtual key code generated by this event

NativeKeyEvent

public NativeKeyEvent(int id,
                      long when,
                      int modifiers,
                      int rawCode,
                      int keyCode,
                      int keyLocation)
Instantiates a new native key event.

Note that passing in an invalid ID results in unspecified behavior.

Parameters:
id - The type of event.
when - The timestamp for the event.
modifiers - the modifier keys down during event. NativeInputEvent _MASK modifiers should be used as they are not compatible with the extended _DOWN_MASK or the old _MASK InputEvent modifiers.
rawCode - The hardware code associated with the native key in this event.
keyCode - The virtual key code generated by this event.
keyLocation - the location ID of the key generating this event.
Method Detail

getRawCode

public int getRawCode()
Returns the hardware code associated with the native key in this event.

Returns:
The hardware code for this event. This is the number used to represent a symbol visible on a keyboard and not the translated key code it may represent.

setRawCode

public void setRawCode(int rawCode)
Set the rawCode value in this event.

Parameters:
rawCode - The native system key for this event. This is the hardware code used to represent a symbol visible on a keyboard and not the translated key code it may represent.

getKeyLocation

public int getKeyLocation()

getKeyText

public static String getKeyText(int keyCode)
Returns a String describing the keyCode, such as "HOME", "F1" or "A". These strings can be localized by changing the awt.properties file.

Parameters:
keyCode - The virtual key code generated by this event
Returns:
A string containing a text description for a physical key, identified by its keyCode.

paramString

public String paramString()
